{"id":"astro-ph/0305269","submitter":"Mattias Marklund","authors":"Mattias Marklund, Gert Brodin, Lennart Stenflo","title":"Electromagnetic wave collapse in a radiation background","comments":"4 pages","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.Lett. 91 (2003) 163601","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.91.163601","report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph gr-qc hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  The nonlinear interaction, due to quantum electrodynamical (QED) effects,\nbetween an electromagnetic pulse and a radiation background is investigated, by\ncombining the methods of radiation hydrodynamics with the QED theory for\nphoton-photon scattering. For the case of a single coherent electromagnetic\npulse we obtain a Zakharov-like system, where the radiation pressure of the\npulse acts as a driver of acoustic waves in the photon gas. For a sufficiently\nintense pulse and/or background energy density there is focusing and subsequent\ncollapse of the pulse. The relevance of our results for various astrophysical\napplications are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 May 2003 13:33:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Oct 2003 16:17:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
